  "structs": {
    "MemoryCap": {
      "index": 0,
      "doc": " Memory capability following Move best practices\n\n Combines:\n - Move Capability Pattern (minimal object = proof)\n - SEAL PrivateData (nonce-based keys)\n - PDW Requirements (app contexts)\n\n Why minimal:\n - Owner can be queried via object ownership\n - Permissions not needed (all caps are read+write)\n - No revocation flag (burn object instead)\n - Follows Move idioms",
      "attributes": [],
      "abilities": [
        "Key",
        "Store"
      ],
      "type_parameters": [],
      "fields": {
        "positional_fields": false,
        "fields": {
          "id": {
